<br><br>

The high-definition wait is over. HD DVD is here, providing six times the resolution of standard DVD with full 1080p resolution and 7.1 surround sound, making images crisper and audio pitch-perfect. HD DVD is based on the original DVD format, taking the best features of DVD and adding a new layer of interactivity that allows for never-before-seen movie experiences. With nearly 150 titles available by the end of 2006, and with HD DVD players for the living room, the PC, and for your Xbox 360 on the market today or in time for holidays, HD DVD provides an easy, affordable transition to high definition.
